# Loading, Empty & Error States Guide

Handle all component states gracefully with Aucctus patterns.

---

## When to Use This Guide

Every component that fetches or displays data needs:
- **Loading states** - While data is being fetched
- **Empty states** - When no data exists
- **Error states** - When something goes wrong

---

## Loading States

### Basic Loading Pattern

```typescript
const Component: React.FC<Props> = ({ uuid }) => {
  const { data, isLoading, isError, error } = useData(uuid);
  
  if (isLoading) return <ComponentSkeleton />;
  if (isError) return <ErrorState error={error} />;
  if (!data) return <EmptyState />;
  
  return <ActualContent data={data} />;
};
```

---

## Skeleton Components

### Creating Skeletons

Skeletons should **mirror the structure** of the actual component:

```typescript
import SkeletonBlock from '@components/Skeleton/ConceptReport/SkeletonBlock';

const ComponentSkeleton: React.FC = () => {
  return (
    <div className='aucctus-bg-primary aucctus-border-secondary rounded-lg border p-6'>
      {/* Header skeleton */}
      <div className='mb-4 flex items-center justify-between'>
        <div className='flex items-center gap-2'>
          <SkeletonBlock className='h-4 w-4 rounded' />
          <SkeletonBlock className='h-4 w-32' />
        </div>
        <SkeletonBlock className='h-8 w-20 rounded-lg' />
      </div>
      
      {/* Content skeleton */}
      <div className='space-y-3'>
        <SkeletonBlock className='h-4 w-full' />
        <SkeletonBlock className='h-4 w-full' />
        <SkeletonBlock className='h-4 w-5/6' />
      </div>
    </div>
  );
};
```

### SkeletonBlock Usage

```typescript
// Basic usage
<SkeletonBlock className='h-4 w-32' />

// Custom background
<SkeletonBlock 
  className='h-8 w-full rounded-lg' 
  backgroundClassName='aucctus-bg-tertiary'
/>

// Multiple blocks
{[...Array(5)].map((_, i) => (
  <SkeletonBlock key={i} className='h-4 w-full' />
))}
```

### Full-Page Loading

```typescript
import { UnifiedLoadingState } from '@components';

const PageComponent: React.FC = () => {
  const { data, isLoading } = usePageData();
  
  if (isLoading) {
    return <UnifiedLoadingState message="Loading your data..." />;
  }
  
  return <PageContent data={data} />;
};
```

### Progressive Loading

Load critical data first, show skeletons for secondary data:

```typescript
const Component: React.FC<Props> = ({ uuid }) => {
  const { data: primary, isLoading: isPrimaryLoading } = usePrimaryData(uuid);
  const { data: secondary, isLoading: isSecondaryLoading } = useSecondaryData(uuid);
  
  // Block on critical data
  if (isPrimaryLoading) {
    return <PrimarySkeleton />;
  }
  
  return (
    <div>
      <PrimaryContent data={primary} />
      
      {/* Show skeleton while secondary loads */}
      {isSecondaryLoading ? (
        <SecondarySkeleton />
      ) : (
        <SecondaryContent data={secondary} />
      )}
    </div>
  );
};
```

