## Fallback Data Patterns

### Semantic Fallbacks

Use semantically appropriate fallbacks:

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD - Semantic fallbacks
const displayData = {
  title: data?.title || 'Untitled',
  description: data?.description || 'No description provided',
  value: data?.value ?? 0,              // 0 for numeric defaults
  status: data?.status || 'pending',
  items: data?.items ?? [],             // Empty array for lists
  timestamp: data?.timestamp || undefined, // undefined for truly missing
};

// ❌ BAD - Fake or misleading data
const displayData = {
  timestamp: data?.timestamp || Date.now(),     // Don't generate fake timestamps
  status: data?.status || 'Complete',           // Don't use status that doesn't match reality
};
```

### Safe Property Access

```typescript
// Optional chaining
const value = data?.nested?.property ?? 'default';

// For uncertain structures
const value = 
  (data && 
   typeof data === 'object' && 
   'property' in data
    ? (data.property as string)
    : null) || 'default value';
```

